    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Use implicit differentiation to find&nbsp; \[\frac{dy}{dx}\] <br>for the graph of&nbsp; \[x^{@n1@}+y^{@n2@}={@n3@}xy.\]</p>
<p>\( \dfrac{dy}{dx} =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>To find \(\dfrac{dy}{dx}\) for the graph of \(x^{@n1@}+y^{@n2@}={@n3@}xy\) rearrange the equation to give:</p>
<p>\[x^{@n1@}+y^{@n2@}-{@n3@}xy =0.\]</p>
<p>Thus:</p>
<p>\[\frac{d}{dx}\left(x^{@n1@}+y^{@n2@}-{@n3@}xy\right) =0\]</p>
<p>\[{@n1@}{@x^(n1-1)@}+{@n2@}{@y^(n2-1)@}\frac{dy}{dx}-{@n3@}(y+x\frac{dy}{dx})=0\]</p>
<p>\[\frac{dy}{dx}({@n2@}{@y^(n2-1)@}-{@n3@}x) = {@n3@}y-{@n1@}{@x^(n1-1)@}\]</p>
<p>\[\frac{dy}{dx} = \frac{{@n3@}y-{@n1@}{@x^(n1-1)@}}{{@n2@}{@y^(n2-1)@}-{@n3@}x}.\]</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
